    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"honoring our humanity\" or doing \"small acts\" doesn't change the fact that the trajectory is set. it's like being a passenger on a ship that's already hit the iceberg but we're all just sitting in the lounge pretending it's fine. it feels so much more honest to just admit that everything is going to collapse. once you accept that, staying around to watch it all fall apart just feels like unnecessary suffering. like, why stay for the disaster?",
